<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>Sir</salute>
</opener>

<lb/><p>No apology was
<lb/>necessary in addressing
<lb/>me on the subject of
<lb/>your note of the <date when="1856-12-10">10<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date> which
<lb/>came to hand today,
<lb/>The influential position
<lb/>you hold in the literary
<lb/>world renders your
<lb/>offer of negotiation quite
<lb/>an honour but I had
<lb/>previously the preference

	<pb facs="liv_000930_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Murray</persName>.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>Accept of my thanks
<lb/>for the kind words of
<lb/>welcome with which
<lb/>you favour me and
<lb/>believe me</p>

<closer>
<lb rend="center"/><salute>Yours faithfully</salute>
<lb rend="right"/><signed><persName>David <choice><orig>Livingston</orig><reg>Livingstone</reg></choice></persName></signed>
</closer>

